Title: Hip Fracture Management  (Trade Cloth)
Author: মার্টিন জে. পার্কার
Summary: Proximal femor fractures (hip fractures) have an incidence of 50,000 a year in England and Wales and approximately 20% of acute orthopaedic beds are occupied by such patients. The incidence of the condition is increasing as the average age of the population moves upward, and greater emphasis on audit has meant that surgeons are under ever-increasing pressure to release hospital beds as quickly as possible. This book aims to review the existing literature as well as to provide clear and practical guidance for both the practising orthopaedic surgeon and the trainee, who is frequently left to deal with the major workload of hip fractures.

Title: Management of Ectopic Pregnancy
Author: রিচার্ড ই. লিচ
Summary: Wayne State Univ., Detroit, MI. Concise office reference presents comprehensive coverage on treating ectopic pregnancy. Includes clinical management pearls. Epidemiology and histopathology are discussed, as well as recent advances in the field. For clinicians and residents. DNLM: Pregnancy, Ectopic--therapy.
